  serving size: 500
---

Trim the @green beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #medium saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char and soften,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn the heat down to medium, then stir in the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}
more.

Once the beans have softened, stir in the @water{200%ml} and @chicken stock
paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil.

When boiling, remove from the heat, stir in the @couscous{120%g} and cover with
a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Leave to the side for ~{8-10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on
medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} and season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks and pop into a #bowl{}. Drizzle
with @olive oil{drizzle} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix well.

Once the chicken is cooked, stir the @korma curry paste{50%g}, @mango chutney{40%g},
half the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} and the @water{50%ml} into the pan.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until slightly thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, share the couscous and beans between your serving #bowls{}.

Spoon the glazed chicken over the top.

Finish with spoonfuls of the tomato salsa and a dollop of the remaining yoghurt.

Enjoy!